restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.name: The Lounge UNSW
restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.address: Level 11, Library (F21), Library Rd, UNSW Sydney, Kensington NSW 2033, Australia

reviews.text:
The place is really nice on the top floor of the UNSW Library building. The view is beautiful, the place is calm and pleasant. People are welcoming.

The food is in the style of fine dining. But not very expensive compared to other fine dining options in Sydney. For a meal, it will cost around $50 with desserts. The food is tasty and there is not a big menu to select from.

As far as on campus eateries go comma this rate among the best I‚Äôve been to in the world. Be sure to get there when they have the hamburger on special menu because they really know how to do it right. No frills and that‚Äôs what you want. Delicious. Also check out the dessert menu, not to Miss!

UNSW's new dining venue - fantastic restaurant to take VIPs for lunch or dinner. Sensational for casual dining, business meetings, coffee or functions. Seating is available inside or outside on the verandah area. I recommend outdoor seating during summer time to take in the picturesque views towards Botany Bay. Exceptional sunset views are best paired with a drink and bar nibbles. Food is always exceptional, whether it be for small or large events. A thoughtfully curated wine list to suit all budgets.

It was a good thing we were there for lunch as the portions were small and the prices relatively high. A tiny serve of cheese (2 small pieces) with crackers and a few raisins was certainly not worth $16. Minimalistic to be kind. Mean otherwise. The quality of the food was fine, the service average, the ambience and view good, though you can't see the view when seated. I get the impression it is intended for people on expense accounts.

An excellent new dining experience on campus and a great place for UNSW staff to enjoy a casual meal, hold a business meeting or celebrate a special occasion. The Lounge offers exceptional service and food quality beyond what is seen in the rest of campus. Located on the top of the main library, not only is this hidden away from the general student population, but the additional balcony offers exception views of the campus below and the city in the distance.

The lounge offers a selection of a la carte options with dessert, wine and tea to come with. With various menus for breakfast, lunch and dinner and a late closing time of 10 pm, this place would be great for any occasion.

reviews.text: It's very ridiculous that these foods on the picture cost me 16 dollars! And this is also a photo of me adding some beef after I have confirmed it with the staff!!!!!!!!!! The taste is very average, and the amount is pitiful. It's not worth eating at all.
Ordered the Char Kway Teow. Absolutely tiny portions, yet same price as other stores. i could see through the food to the bottom of the bowl, which is a mini one too.

food was good, the vegetables were bitter so i wouldn't recommend that‚Äì a bit stingy on the portions of wontons, not as advertised but overall the taste was good. each section had a completely different taste palette to the next so if you like coherence it won't be for you.

Food is ok,a  bin chicken took my food but that was not the shop's fault (those evil dirty birds were so brutal when stealing people food from the hands) that is why the atmosphere is so uncomfortable to eat there.
Staffs are not friendly and rarely say thank you. Customer service needs to be improved. But I found that is the uniform customer service style of all Papa rich shops I have been to.
I ordered 3 chicken rice but I just get one chicken! So bad!!! I‚Äôll not order with this restaurant again!

The taste is home-style and delicious, cheaper than off-campus options. No need to go far after class, they‚Äôre ready quickly so you can eat while it‚Äôs hot. Total go-to for UNSW students!
Nice place to get food in the uni, very affordable with many options üëå
Very friendly staff, always love the food ((esp Honey Chicken)) :) üòã

Options without bones are best imo. Not sure how I feel about all the single use plastic containers they are using.
Budget friendly

restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.name: Southern Wok
restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.address: LG 58 Morven Brown Building University of, Kensington NSW 2033, Australia

reviews.text:
Upon entry to this restaurant, I was in a bad mood due to the harsh Sydney weather. However, the aura of this place was quite uplifting; with the  smell indicating the home made aspect of the meals .
I opted for the classic choice of ‚ÄúHainanese Chicken Tasty Rice - $16.5 ‚Äù. The order arrived quite quickly. I was slightly disappointed with the portions to be honest but that was quickly resolved upon tasting. One orders this meal when they require a hearty meal, which luckily was the case here. The chicken is boiled and steamed to perfection. Accompanied by well seasoned scallions, this dish is just a great comfort food. The flavours blend together creating a tasty concoction. Evidently, a mix of chicken and rice should normally be quite good; this place turns it into a delectable meal.

I would however recommend having a more balanced marination of the chicken as it does at parts lack flavour. Overall, I was quite pleased with this experience.

As for the place itself; the indoor seating area feels quite crammed and gets very hot on certain days. The outdoor seating is lovely though and balances out the weather on a hot day such as the day of this review. I was delighted to have this option.

3.8/5*

Food and academia both possess high levels of priority for the Feed Punchers, often being in conjunction with one another. Another academic Feed Punch saw the Feed Punchers landing at Southern Wok, located in the mid to upper campus of UNSW.

-The roast duck was roasted to perfection with great crispy skin, maintaining a sweet and salty dark-soy flavour. Sided with a moist steamed bok choy, which helped balance the saltiness.

-The Shanghai noodles were extremely diverse, featuring beef, prawns and chicken. There was a strong fish sauce taste and  an addition of bok choy and crunchy onion. A bit of extra spice would have empowered this dish greatly.

-The Hainan chicken was poached to perfection. It was extremely soft and delicate in the mouth, giving off simple but effective flavours of ginger, garlic and chicken broth.

-The Shandong chicken was a little light on seasoning and flavour, but the chicken was yet again, cooked to perfection. Also served with bok choy and rice, alike the other dishes.

-The fried rice had chicken in it which was quite unique, differing from classic pork fried rices. It had nice tastes of spring onion, egg and subtle flavours from the prawns.

-The BBQ pork was tender but lacked in flavour. The one served with rice had a slight salty-soy-chilli taste, however, the one served with noodles was extremely flavourless.

Overall, this was a nice, quick, academic feed, which offered some well cooked meals, just slightly falling short of flavour in some areas. Thanks Southern Wok!

Love the food - always cure my homesickness. The combo egg sauce noodles and fried beef noodles are the best. Love the ladies and gentlemen work here too. Always super friendly and welcoming :) thank you

Too much MSG. I swear I was completely foggy and lightheaded for an hour after finishing the noodle soup. This is definitely not just a carb crash ‚Äî I‚Äôve always been super sensitive to MSG. The broth would taste even better with less seasoning.

A lovely, cosy, home-made feel restaurant in the bustling upper campus of UNSW. One of my favourites, with clean seating and cutlery and a wide selection of food. Most recently, however, the food quantities per order have been decreasing, specifically for take-away orders. There is too much rice and not enough meat.
The restaurant still earns 4 stars, although heavily debated, as I recently found two hairs in my meal.
I recommend the Pad See Eew. I also recommend hairnets for the kitchen!

restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.name: Dolce Fiori
restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.address: 52 St Pauls St, Randwick NSW 2031, Australia

reviews.text:
One of those places when you go visit once, stays with you and you can‚Äôt wait to return again.
Because ‚Ä¶the place is Happy. It has a vibe. It‚Äôs on its own . It has a theatrical energy and you feel like you are in the amusement park.. somehow.
Wonderful Mario is there to look after you and he will go around and make sure everyone is having a good time and as well enjoying their food. Very lovely and so kind staff was looking after us as well.
We definitely did Enjoyed. Delicious food and incredibly tasty Italian wine .. such a treat. Wonderful value . Totally recommend.
Sydney‚Äôs hidden gem.

Had a phenomenal time here tonight. The food and service was 5 star. Rasu and the new server really made our night. They even gave us little chocolate treats when we didn‚Äôt want dessert and were so accommodating when we wanted to move outside. Would definitely recommend and will be back!!

We had a mum and son dinner. My 5yo son said he wished he could give a 5 star rating. He said especially because they were so nice to us and because the place was super pretty and nice.
I enjoyed my steak with potatoes and salad. I couldn‚Äôt finish the whole steak. We are visiting from out of area for the children‚Äôs hospital. Thanks for cheering us up.

You are truly missing out if you don‚Äôt plan a dinner date night at Dolce Fiorii. I went with my gals and had the most wonderful time. The wine was smooth. The food was delicious. The venue is aesthetically on point! But what made the evening that extra special was restaurant owner Mario checking in on everyone and having a wonderful chat with some definite wise words from a wise man! It was a 10/10 experience on a Tuesday night! I cannot wait to go back

Visited on the 29/04/2025

Very good customer service and staff were friendly as well as fast service. Also not to mention they serve great cocktails and food especially the pizzas. Restaurant atmosphere is very aesthetically pleasing with neon lights. I recommend this place if you are hanging around the spot looking for a great meal.

restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.name: Laksa Delight
restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.address: Mathew's Arcade, University of New South Wales, High St, Kensington NSW 2033, Australia

reviews.text:
Worst services ever.  The dishes without rice is even more expensive than if they were with rice. They say that the groceries are more expensive than rice. Worst excuse ever.  I never heard that excuse in any other restaurants. This place should be named Laksa Dismay, Laksa Displease, or Laksa Disgust.

I would give them 0 stars or even negative stars if Google Reviews allowed me to do so.  I hope this place closes down for good.

This is the best Laksa I've ever had, you can really tell the chefs put time, love & effort into their food.

This is a must try!

The photos don't do this food justice, the fried chicken is also a must try!!

This review has been over 20 years in the making. My first experience of this incredible laksa was in my first year uni at UNSW in 2000. I still remember the no nonsense malaysian aunties who took care of this lowly undergrad. It's been there for me through thick and thin, through uni, and exams. The soup was delicious, rumoured to be so addictive there could've been drugs in there we joked. But it was all love and authenticity. I order mine just egg noodles and soy chicken. This laksa has and will be the gold standard by which I measure all other laksas.
I was pleased to discover that while the place has changed hands since, the quality was the same.
You'll laugh, you'll cry, and most of all you'll love.

A hidden gem within Sydney. I love visiting this place when I‚Äôm in Sydney. There is always queues for their laksa no matter the time of day. It is delicious, spicy and flavorsome. They use a combination of rice and hokkien noodles in the soups. The choices of meat available ranges from beef, chicken, pork, wontons and seafood. Make sure you slurp every drop of your soup because I will guarantee you would be asking for more. The store is open throughout the year but close during summer university break.
Time and time again this place does not disappoint when it comes to laksa. Always full of flavour and you're greeted with a smile every time. My fave food place on UNSW campus.

restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.name: Stellini Pasta Bar
restaurantsWithPhotoUrls.address: Gate 2, 11 High St, Kensington NSW 2033, Australia

reviews.text: Tried this spot for the first time and overall it was a decent experience. We ordered a bacon pizza and a chicken one. Both were alright‚Äînot bad, but nothing particularly memorable either. The crust was cooked well and the cheese was gooood, but the flavours didn‚Äôt quite pop the way we were hoping. Service was friendly and quick, and the place was clean with a nice vibe. Might give it another shot to try something different on the menu. Solid, but room for improvement.

This place is incredible!! I‚Äôve been looking for a new pasta place since every other Italian restaurant is way too overpriced these days (and hardly authentic), so I ordered from here and it‚Äôs AMAZING. This is the most authentic tasting pasta I‚Äôve had since my trip to Italy. Huge portions and you can tell they don‚Äôt cut corners with their ingredients. Best part is that it‚Äôs reasonably priced!

Absolutely incredible food and coffee! Nimesh is super friendly and always goes above and beyond ‚Äì not to mention he makes amazing food. The atmosphere is cozy, and everything on the menu is full of flavor. Easily one of my favorite spots ‚Äì highly recommend!

I don't study at UNSW, but this pasta place is just the best in town for what the price is. My go-to pastas are carbonara and bolognese. PLUS their soup of the day (it's always pumpkin soup) sooo yummy!

Had pesto and carbonara. Very authentic and delicious food with decent portion and price! Definitely good choice for weekday meals!
Fungi is great as well! This has been our all time fav lunch spot on campus!
Update: Spinachi is my new fav now! It goes really well with penne because the sauce will be stuffed inside the noodles! Go try it!

I seriously love everything about this place. It‚Äôs run by the sweetest older couple who are always so friendly and chatty. You can tell they work really hard and genuinely care about what they do which just makes the vibe even better.

The coffee is always spot on. Smooth, strong, and just consistently good. It‚Äôs the kind of place where you can rely on your order being perfect every time. Their food is just as good. I always recommend the bacon and egg roll. And the huge muffins which are the best afternoon snack. You honestly can‚Äôt go wrong with anything on the menu.

I come here pretty much every day. It‚Äôs cozy, welcoming, and reminds me of home. I really wish more people knew about this place and the university needs more independent places like this. If you‚Äôre in the area, definitely check it out.

Waited in line with two others, and the owner seemed rushed and flustered‚Äîjust tapping cards and moving people along without saying a single word. Zero interaction, zero courtesy. Ordered a ham croissant, which was reheated by squashing it into a flat, soggy mess. Easily the worst croissant I‚Äôve ever had. Thanks for wasting my $8.
Coffee was alright but the custard tart had such a strange texture. I can only assume they put gelatin in the custard.

I'm craving nutella donut, and here I amüòç
Chewy and has a full nutella inside. Worth to tryüòç
Thank you for your smile as well when you ask my order.

Bought a sausage roll and it tasted off so I told 6 OF MY FRIENDS to smell it, they all say it‚Äôs sour while I‚Äôm still trying to gulp the first bite down. I go to the people working and one of them says ‚Äúit‚Äôs not off it‚Äôs just pork/beef it‚Äôs normal‚Äù but they give me another roll which I didn‚Äôt have the appetite for. I was throwing up the whole night from that single bite and I didn‚Äôt even eat anything else that day

Every other time before I just got told lemon was a dressing, so thats all I asked for. If youre gonna be a stubborn little Sh!t because of some dressing names, dont work. I shouldnt have to ask just put any dressing 5 times for me to get my food, and I dont understand how stingy you guys are. In total i got 3 pieces of beef in my salad. And 60% of my bowl is rocket leaf. Thank you guys very much.
